<h2>0.3 How we teach</h2>
<p class="prose-columns">
This section is for kids and grown-ups both. We use a method that starts
with something you can touch or picture, and only then moves to code: first
something concrete, like counting blocks; then a picture of the same idea,
like a diagram; and only then the actual Python code that does it. Each
chapter also opens with a few guided questions before we explain
anything &ndash; try to answer them yourself first. Mistakes are part of how
this works. We say &ldquo;not yet,&rdquo; never &ldquo;wrong.&rdquo; Every
chapter ends with two short checks: a self-graded &ldquo;Check My
Knowledge&rdquo; quiz, and a challenge that mixes in ideas from earlier
chapters, so you keep old skills sharp while you learn new ones.
</p>
